you this Key Stone, right?

00:03:36.249 --> 00:03:38.585
Key Stone?

00:03:38.585 --> 00:03:41.421
I'm sorry, but I'm afraid
I can't.

00:03:41.421 --> 00:03:44.825
If there's anything else I can
help you with, I'd be happy to.

00:03:44.825 --> 00:03:47.227
But, this Key Stone is part of
the bond I have with Gardevoir.

00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:52.132
‐ Bond?
‐ I can't lend it to anyone.

00:03:52.132 --> 00:03:54.501
‐ Sorry.
‐ I understand how you feel..

00:03:54.501 --> 00:03:56.870
But please..

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:59.906
Alright then, well,
how about the next time

00:03:59.906 --> 00:04:02.275
I visit Lumiose City,
if I have some time‐‐

00:04:02.275 --> 00:04:04.177
KATHI LEE
Not going to happen. No way!

00:04:04.177 --> 00:04:07.147
Diantha's schedule
is already jam‐packed.

00:04:07.147 --> 00:04:10.117
Right now, we haven't any plans
to visit Lumiose City.

00:04:10.117 --> 00:04:11.852
Your expression is as cute
as ever

00:04:11.852 --> 00:04:13.019
when you get angry you know..

00:04:13.019 --> 00:04:15.989
[groans]

00:04:15.989 --> 00:04:18.425
Why don't we discuss
this whole scheduling conflict

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:20.494
in a civilized way over
a little dinner?

00:04:20.494 --> 00:04:22.796
KATHI LEE
No, thanks.

00:04:22.796 --> 00:04:25.732
You're on soon.
Are you all set to go?

00:04:25.732 --> 00:04:28.168
Yes, you're all welcome to stay
for the exhibition battle.

00:04:30.437 --> 00:04:32.739
Ohh.
[AMAZED]

00:04:35.008 --> 00:04:36.243
ANNOUNCER
And now,

00:04:36.243 --> 00:04:37.677
for today's main event..

00:04:38.645 --> 00:04:41.448
Please welcome our Trainers!

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:44.084
'Crowned Best of Brackish Town
just last year..'

00:04:44.084 --> 00:04:46.419
...say hi to Magnus!

00:04:46.419 --> 00:04:48.255
He'll be facing off
against the elegant

00:04:48.255 --> 00:04:50.824
Kalos region Champion,
Diantha.'

00:04:50.824 --> 00:04:52.359
[crowd cheering]

00:04:52.359 --> 00:04:54.161
‐ Yeah!
‐ Yay, Diantha!

00:04:57.364 --> 00:04:59.099
Professor, what's with
that Key Stone

00:04:59.099 --> 00:05:01.067
you two were
talking about before?

00:05:01.067 --> 00:05:03.336
You see, the Key Stone
is crucial for a Pokémon

00:05:03.336 --> 00:05:06.006
to Mega Evolve.

00:05:06.006 --> 00:05:09.176
The stone a Trainer possesses
is called a Key Stone.

00:05:09.176 --> 00:05:10.544
And the stone a Pokémon
possesses

00:05:10.544 --> 00:05:12.179
is called a Mega Stone.

00:05:12.179 --> 00:05:14.114
Key Stone and Mega Stone.

00:05:14.114 --> 00:05:16.483
Alright, Gardevoir, it's time.

00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.685
Let's show the fans
a spectacular battle.

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:21.822
[APPEARING]

00:05:21.822 --> 00:05:23.356
The Champion's Pokémon.

00:05:23.356 --> 00:05:25.859
[AMAZED]

00:05:25.859 --> 00:05:28.862
POKEDEX
Gardevoir, the Embrace Pokémon.

00:05:28.862 --> 00:05:31.698
'Gardevoir will use all
of its psychic energy'

00:05:31.698 --> 00:05:33.033
'to protect a Trainer it has
made a deep connection with.'

00:05:35.702 --> 00:05:38.371
Hey, look! Gardevoir's wearing
a pendant as well.

00:05:38.371 --> 00:05:39.840
Yeah, you're right!

00:05:39.840 --> 00:05:42.342
That's Gardevoir's Mega Stone.

00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:45.011
Mega Stones have many different
names, depending on the Pokémon

00:05:45.011 --> 00:05:47.180
that Mega Evolves.

00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:49.649
In Gardevoir's case, its Mega
Stone is known as Gardevoirite.

00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.689
I see! As long as you have both
a Key Stone and a Mega Stone

00:05:55.689 --> 00:05:57.724
a Pokémon can Mega Evolve.

00:05:57.724 --> 00:06:01.494
‐ So cool.
‐ 'That's actually not enough.'

00:06:01.494 --> 00:06:02.495
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE
'A Pokémon can't Mega Evolve

00:06:02.495 --> 00:06:04.164
unless the hearts'

00:06:04.164 --> 00:06:05.699
of Trainer and Pokémon
become one.

00:06:05.699 --> 00:06:07.968
Hearts become one?

00:06:07.968 --> 00:06:09.736
It means they need to have
an exceptionally

00:06:09.736 --> 00:06:11.571
strong bond between them.

00:06:11.571 --> 00:06:13.373
Of course!

00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:14.507
'That's what
Diantha meant when she said'

00:06:14.507 --> 00:06:15.709
'the Key Stone is part
of their bond.'

00:06:17.878 --> 00:06:21.314
Hmm, it sounds like
the Champion's Gardevoir

00:06:21.314 --> 00:06:23.550
possesses the power
to Mega Evolve.

00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:26.553
Yeah! That's what
I'm talkin' about.

00:06:26.553 --> 00:06:28.989
Diantha's a great actress,
just like myself.

00:06:28.989 --> 00:06:31.658
Oh, how did I forget that?

00:06:31.658 --> 00:06:36.296
A fellow great actress's Pokémon
is worthy to be my Pokémon.

00:06:36.296 --> 00:06:39.633
And Gardevoir will be
my Pokémon, mark my word.

00:06:39.633 --> 00:06:41.768
Marked! In addition,
the Boss will love a Pokémon

00:06:41.768 --> 00:06:43.036
that can Mega Evolve.

00:06:43.036 --> 00:06:44.838
Now! Absol, let's go.

00:06:46.606 --> 00:06:48.375
[APPEARING]

00:06:48.375 --> 00:06:50.410
Gardevoir and Absol.

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:52.679
POKEDEX
Absol. The Disaster Pokémon.

00:06:52.679 --> 00:06:55.148
'When disasters are detected
with its horn

00:06:55.148 --> 00:06:57.350
'Absol comes down from
the mountains to warn people.'

